<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Singapore leaders Meet Macao SAR Chief Executive </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Singapore Prime Minister Goh
Chok Tong and Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew met separately with
visiting Chief Executive of China's Macao Special Administrative
Region Edmund Ho Hau Wah Thursday.
</P>
<P>
He told reporters after the meetings that they talked about
Macao during the two separate conversations in which Ho briefed
the two leaders about what has been happening in Macao after the
unification and how "one country, two systems" works in Macao.
</P>
<P>
"Both of them expressed their explicit support for Macao and
said that the Singapore government would be very pleased to carry
out serious cooperation with Macao," he said.
</P>
<P>
He quoted Singapore Senior Minister Lee Kuan Yew as saying
that "under cautious conditions, Singapore should help Macao in
training its civil servants."
</P>
<P>
Ho Hau Wah will return home Friday after winding up his three-
day official visit to Singapore. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
