<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, August 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS -- French fishermen blocking vehicle access to the
Channel Tunnel in protest against high fuel prices lifted the
blockade at Coquelles, Pas-de-Calais, early Thursday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The lifting came after French Minister of Agriculture Jean
Glavany announced a comprehensive plan of compensation for the
fishermen, including a cut of social charges and costs for using
port facilities by the fishermen. (Europe-Tunnel-Blockade)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS -- The European Central Bank (ECB) on Thursday raised
its key interest rate by 0.25 percentage points to 4.5 percent in
a bid to ease the pressure of a rising inflation in the 11-nation
single currency area.
</P>
<P>
It is imperative that medium-term upward pressure on prices be
contained, said the bank in a statement after a Governing Council
meeting. (ECB-Rate-Rise)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- A local court in Indonesia on Thursday was forced to
postpone the trial on the corruption case of former Indonesian
President Soeharto until September 14, due to the defendant's
absence for health reasons.
</P>
<P>
At the court room, Soeharto's lawyers read a medical report to
justify his failure to attend Thursday morning's hearing in the
South Jakarta District Court. (Indonesia-Soeharto Trial)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LAGOS -- Five of the 11 British soldiers held hostage by
militiamen in Sierra Leone have been released, the British
Broadcasting Cooperation reported on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The BBC quoted a British army spokesman as saying that the five
are safe and on their way to the capital Freetown. (SLeone-
Britain )
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- Russia on Thursday condemned Estonia's decision to
expel two Russian diplomats for what Tallinn said activities
incompatible with their status, saying it would evict two Estonian
diplomats in response.
</P>
<P>
"Estonia has blamed two Russian diplomats for 'activities not
befitting their status' and proposed that they leave the country
within 48 hours," the Interfax news agency quoted a Russian
Foreign Ministry statement as saying. (Russian-Estonia-Diplomats)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- The Philippine government said Thursday that the
kidnapping of American Jeffrey Schilling by the Abu Sayyaf
guerrilla will not affect the ongoing negotiations for the release
of the remaining six European and one Filipino of the hostages
earlier seized.
</P>
<P>
Presidential spokesman Ricardo Puno said this point has been
confirmed by Abu Sayyaf leader Ghalib Andang, alias Commander
Robot, during their latest talks with chief government negotiator
Robert Aventajado. (Philippines-Hostage)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MANILA -- Thirteen people were injured in an explosion in the
southern Philippines Thursday afternoon, the ABS-CBN television
reported.
</P>
<P>
It said a bomb made of five mortar shells exploded at around 4:
50 p.m. outside a bus terminal in Kabacan town of Cotabato
province.  (Philippines-Explosion)  
</P>
