<HEADLINE> Bossoni Wins Sixth Stage at Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Italian Paolo Bossoni claimed the
first victory in his professional career on the 155.5 km sixth
stage of the Tour of Spain between Benidorm and Valencia on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Cantina Tollo rider chose the best line in the final 50
metres to beat sprint specialists Spain's Oscar Freire and Italian
Giovanni Lombardi.
</P>
<P>
The competition had been poised to be battled out between
Lombardi and Freire but young second-year pro Bossoni swept
through on the right-hand side to steal the win. 
</P>
</TEXT>
