<HEADLINE> Devers Pulls out of Berlin Meeting for Injury </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
BERLIN, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Injury forced Olympic champion
Gail Devers to pull out of Friday's Berlin Golden League meeting,
according to meeting director Rudi Thiel on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"It's just a slight strain in her hamstring but she doesn't
want to take any risks with Sydney fast approaching and we fully
understand that," Rudi Thiel was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The 33-year-old Devers won 100 metres gold at the last two
Olympics but now concentrates on the 100 hurdles.
</P>
<P>
She has already made sure of a part of a jackpot of 50 kilos
in gold bars to be shared between the athletes who win their
events at five out of the seven Golden League meetings.
</P>
<P>
Berlin is the final round of the series and also the last
major event before the Sydney Olympics.  
</P>
</TEXT>
