<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 2000 GMT, September 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak named outgoing
Deputy Chief of General Staff Uzi Dayan as new head of National
Security Council, or Israel's diplomatic planning unit, late
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
Local analysts said that the move boosted Dayan's chances to be
chosen as successor of the current Israel Defense Forces (IDF)
Chief of General Staff Shaul Mofaz, who is scheduled to step down
next July, Israel's Jerusalem Post and Ha'aretz daily both
reportedFriday.
</P>
<P>
In April, Mofaz, who reportedly is at odds with Dayan, named IDF
Central Commander Moshe Ya'alon to replace him as new Deputy Chief
of General Staff, claiming that he just wanted to explore more
candidates as his successors. (Israel-Security Head)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Prime Minister Ehud Barak said Friday that
he did not know any evidence of imminent missiles attacks from
Iraq, but Israel is always ready for the possibility.
</P>
<P>
Earlier reports said that a U.S. Army Patriot anti-missile
battery in Germany was on alert for possible raid against Israel,
because Iraq, as the U.S. officials said, wanted to launch attacks
against the Jewish state during the political vacuum in Washington
in the next few weeks for presidential elections.
</P>
<P>
However, Barak, quoted by Israel Radio, said during a tour to
schools in central Israel, "I am not sure any more that we must
truly be worried and I don't know whether this Patriot battery must
truly be worried." (Israel-Iraq-Potential Attack)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egyptian Foreign Minister Amr Moussa will lead his
country's delegation to the United Nations millennium summit in New
York, Egypt's official Middle East News Agency reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Moussa, who will be in place of President Hosni Mubarak, will
fly to New York on Tuesday for the summit, due to be held on
September 6-8, the news agency quoted an unnamed Foreign Ministry
official as saying.
</P>
<P>
Due to busy schedules at home, the Egyptian president has
canceled a plan to take part in the millennium summit along with
leaders of more than 100 countries, reports have said. (Egypt-UN-
Summit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Renowned jurist Noeman Gomma was elected on Friday as
president of the New Wafd Party, Egypt's main opposition party, the
country's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Gomma, who has been the party's first vice president since the
early 1990s, succeeds Fouad Seragedin, a long-time leader who died
on August 9.
</P>
<P>
He was backed by 500 of the 843 members of the party general
assembly, with Seragedin's grandson, Fouad Badrawi, assistant
secretary general of the party, taking the second place with 129
votes to lead two other candidates, the news agency said.  (Egypt-
Opposition Party-New Leader) 
</P>
</TEXT>
