<HEADLINE> Arafat to Brief Arab FMs on Palestinian-Israeli Negotiations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat
is due to brief Arab foreign ministers Sunday on the latest
developments of the peace talks with Israel, a senior Arab League
(AL) official said on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Arafat, who will deliver a speech to a meeting of the AL Foreign
Ministers Council in Cairo Sunday, is also to keep the Arab
officials posted on the outcome of his recent world tour, Saed
Kamal, AL assistant secretary general, said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat has visited more than 20 countries in a bid to win
support for the Palestinian stance on the Mideast peace process
since July 25 when the U.S.-sponsored Palestinian-Israeli Camp
David summit failed to reach a final peace deal due to disputes
over the status of Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinian leader will consult with the ministers and
permanent delegates to the pan-Arab forum on ways of pushing the
Mideast peace talks forward, Kamal said.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians want East Jerusalem as the capital of their
future independent state under the United Nations Security Council
Resolution 242 which rules that this sector of the holy city is
part of the Arab territories occupied by Israel in the 1967 Mideast
War and must be returned. Arab countries support the Palestinian
demand. 
