<HEADLINE> South Africa Sets September as National Malaria Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The South African
Department of Health Friday reminded the public that September --
the beginning of the malaria transmission season -- is National
Malaria Awareness month.
</P>
<P>
The department said in a statement that the theme of the
campaign, which is the first of its kind, is "Malaria can be
prevented -- use a bed net".
</P>
<P>
The statement said that a study conducted by the Medical
Research Council (MRC) showed that bed nets could effectively
prevent malaria.
</P>
<P>
"Bed nets usage in the high risk malaria areas will now
complement indoor residual spraying, thus providing more
protection to the individual," said the statement.
</P>
<P>
The study found that the occurrence of malaria increased by 31
percent in areas where bed nets were not used, while it only rose
by 18 percent in areas where the nets were used.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, bed nets would this year be
introduced in high risk areas such as Mpumalanga, Northern
Province and parts of KwaZulu-Natal. 
</P>
</TEXT>
