<DOCNO> XIE20000901.0047 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> No Final Report on Concorde Crash in Months: Investigator </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The chief French investigator
for the crash of Air France Concorde said Friday that no final
report explaining the cause of the crash will be published in
months or even years.
</P>
<P>
Paul-Louis Arslanian, director of the Bureau of Accident
Investigation (BEA), told the press that the bureau is still
analyzing the problem about the tire on the undercarriage of the
Concorde which apparently burst when it was taking off.
</P>
<P>
The crash, which took place on July 25 in Gonesse near Paris,
killed all 113 people on board, most of them German tourists.
</P>
<P>
The primary investigation report published by the BEA Thursday
night said that a 43-centimeter metal piece on the runway could
have cut the tire, causing a chain reaction including the outbreak
of a fire on the rear part of the supersonic plane.
</P>
<P>
Investigators said that the runway was cleaned up twice on the
day of the accident, but a final cleaning up was delayed because
of an exercise of several vehicles of firefighters which ran on
the runway.
</P>
<P>
France and Britain, the only two countries which used Concorde
in civil aviation, have suspended flight of the plane permanently.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
