<HEADLINE> IOC Names Evaluation Commission for 2008 Olympic Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The International Olympic
Committee(IOC) today announced the composition of the Evaluation
Commission that will review the qualifications of the candidate
cities to host the Games of the 29th Olympiad in 2008.
</P>
<P>
The commission is composed of external experts and
representatives of the IOC, National Olympic Committees (NOCs),
International Federations (IFs), athletes, and for the first time,
of one representative of the International Paralympic Committee (
IPC), according to a IOC press release.
</P>
<P>
The commission will meet to organize its work and then conduct
on-the-ground analysis of the five candidate cities: Beijing,
Istanbul, Osaka, Paris, and Toronto, between mid-February and mid-
April.
</P>
<P>
Hein Verbruggen takes the chairmanship and Gilbert Felli is the
vice chairman. The members are: IOC representatives Francisco J.
Elizalde, Mario Pescante, and Craig Reedie Cbe, IF representatives
MrsEls Van Breda Vriesman of the International Hockey Federation,
Patrick Baumann of the International Basketball Federation and
MrsCatrin Norinder of the International Equestrian Federation, NOC
representatives Carlos Arthur Nuzman, Tomas Sithole and Bob
Elphinston, Athlete representative Sergei Bubka, Specialists
SimonBalderstone for Environment and Rocky YOON, IPC
representative Robert McCullough, IOC Administration Ms Jacqueline
Barrett. 
</P>
</TEXT>
