<HEADLINE> NE City Celebrates 2,300th Anniversary of Foundation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Over 5,000 local citizens
attended today's parade, watching dozens of floats, travel around
the City Government Square of Shenyang, capital of northeastern
Liaoning Province, to celebrate the 2,300th anniversary of its
founding.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony started at 9:30 a.m. and people dressed in
beautiful costumes from different periods of China's feudal
society walking in the parade attracted large crowds of people.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said archeologists believe the city was
founded 300 years before Christ during the Warring States period (
475 B.C.-221 B.C.), where the Yan Kingdom first set up its capital.
</P>
<P>
It was also the capital of the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911) for
many years. The city started to familiarize the local people with
the wedding and funeral culture and customs from the Qing Dynasty
in 1998 by holding mass parades on holidays.
</P>
<P>
The city government gives the local citizens a day off to
celebrate the city's day. The people celebrate in the evening as
well. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
