<HEADLINE> Leaders of Macao, Singapore Agree to Increase Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of Singapore and the
Macao Special Administrative Region (SAR) of China have agreed to
increase cooperation in economy, trade, tourism and civil servant
training.
</P>
<P>
Edmund Ho Hau Wah, chief executive of the Macao SAR, said atthe
Macao International Airport on Friday following his four-day visit
to Singapore: "I believe the visit will make the contacts of the
two areas more close in the future."
</P>
<P>
He noted that Florinda da Rosa Silva Chan, secretary for
administration and justice of the Macao SAR government, and other
officials will soon go to Singapore and carry out practical
cooperation in the training of civil servants.
</P>
<P>
In view of different social conditions, Macao will not copy the
mode of administration of Singapore, but will learn from its
experience in civil servant training, Edmund Ho said. 
</P>
