<HEADLINE> First Fee-Free Zone Designated in S China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The first part of the Nanning
New and High-tech Development Zone was designated today in south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region to offer fee exemptions
for incoming businesses.
</P>
<P>
The first group of 40 Chinese and foreign enterprises to settle
in the zone will be exempt from 17 administrative charges such as
the land right change fee and urban construction fee.
</P>
<P>
The requirement for the beneficiaries include registration at
the local government, meet the State environment standards and
have a considerable production scale.
</P>
<P>
The move is to help improve the investment environment, reduce
the operations cost of enterprises and adapt to international
practice, said a local government official.
</P>
<P>
More than 800 businesses were settled at the Nanning New and
High-tech Development Zone between 1988 when the zone was
designated and August this year. They generated a combined
industrial output value of 6.8 billion yuan in the period.
</P>
</TEXT>
