<DOCNO> XIE20000901.0053 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Strikes against Pyramid Schemes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The General Office of the
State Council (GOSC) urged governments at all levels to take
effective measures to crack down on pyramid schemes and other
illicit activities.
</P>
<P>
The requirement was raised in a document transmitted today by
the GOSC. Pyramid schemes have reappeared in various parts of
China recently, causing a great financial loss to many people who
were involved in them and disrupting the country's economic and
social order. Some pyramid scheme networks have developed into
underworld gangs, according to a GOSC document.
</P>
<P>
The document called on the industrial and commercial
administration departments to outlaw pyramid schemes or disguised
pyramid scheme networks. The banks should render an active
coordination.
</P>
<P>
With the approval from industrial and commercial administration
departments at or above the county level, the lower level
departments should notify relevant banks to temporarily suspend
the settlement operation of the networks which engage in pyramid
schemes, it said.
</P>
<P>
The public security departments throughout the country should
enhance the management of the transient population and on houses
for rent.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
