<HEADLINE> Fire-Control Website Launched in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- China's first fire control
website was launched today by the China Fire Control Society in
Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The website, www.china-fire.net, offers various information and
the latest news on fire control around the world in both English
and Chinese, as well as research results, rules and laws on fire
fighting in other countries.
</P>
<P>
The website was under the supervision of the Shanghai Fire
Control Scientific Research Institute affiliated with the Ministry
of Public Security. 
</P>
