<HEADLINE> India to Purchase Crude from Nigeria </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- In the first ever term
contract for African crude, India Friday signed a deal for
purchase of 2 million tons of low sulphur crude, the Indian Oil
Corporation (IOC) said.
</P>
<P>
The contract was signed between the IOC and Nigerian National
Petroleum Corporation (NNPC) in Abuja, Nigeria, the IOC said.
</P>
<P>
India imports low sulphur oil to the extent of 20 million tons
annually. As per the official selling price, India will get the
lowest price offered by NNPC to any of its customers. 
</P>
