<HEADLINE> India Operationalises Automatic Route </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Indian government Friday
operationalised automatic approval route for companies raising
upto 50 million U.S. dollars from overseas market through external
commercial borrowings (ECBs) and for refinancing existing ECBs.
</P>
<P>
An official statement said that the move, aimed at shoring up
foreign exchange reserves, would allow companies to raise 50
million dollars from the overseas markets without the prior
approval of the Finance Ministry or the Reserve Bank of India (RBI)
.
</P>
<P>
Under the automatic route arrangement, corporates entity will
henceforth be eligible to enter loan arrangement with overseas
lenders for raising fresh ECB in compliance with ECB rules of the
government or RBI. 
</P>
</TEXT>
