<BODY>
<HEADLINE> South Africa to Raise Fuel Price  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 1 (Xinhua)--South African
motorists will from next Wednesday again have to dig deeper into
their pockets, as the retail petrol price will jump an additional
6 cents (about 0.9 U.S. cent) a litre.
</P>
<P>
The wholesale price of diesel will climb 15 cents (about 2.1 U.
S. cents).a litre, and illuminating paraffin 14 cents (about 2
cents) a litre from September 6, the South African department of
mineral and energy affairs confirmed in a statement on Friday.
</P>
<P>
A litre of petrol in Gauteng would cost 3.66 rand (about 0.52
U.S. dollar) a litre and 3.55 rand (about 0.51 U.S. dollar) a
litre at the coast.
</P>
<P>
The department blamed the increases on higher average
international fuel prices.
</P>
<P>
The South African rand had also weakened slightly over the
period under review -- July 26 to August 25.
</P>
<P>
The monthly petrol price increases have accelerated in 2000,
with a litre of leaded petrol costing 2.90 rand (about 0.40 dollar
)in Gauteng on the first day of the year, an increase of 76 cents
(about 0.11 dollar) a litre.
</P>
<P>
The sharp rise has been attributed to a shortage in global oil
stocks.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
