<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan to Set up 4 Military Areas Against Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Kazakhstan will set up four
military areas and new mobile troops to deal with intrusion by
terrorists, President Nursultan Nazarbayev said Friday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in parliament, Nazarbayev said his country will
increase military budget this year, which will at least account
for 1 percent of the gross domestic product next year, according
to Interfax News Agency.
</P>
<P>
He asked all Kazakh people and political forces in the country
to unite against threat of violence and instability in Central
Asia.
</P>
<P>
Starting early last month, many groups of terrorists intruded
into the border areas of Uzbekistan and Kyrgyzstan, provoking
military conflicts there.
</P>
<P>
Nazarbayev also said Kazakhstan, which has about 1,800
religious organizations, should pay attention to religious
problems.
</P>
<P>
Kazakhstan must make legislation against the spread of
religious extremist thoughts, he said. 
</P>
