<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mongolia to Hold Local Elections in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian parliament
decided Friday that local elections would be held on October 1.
</P>
<P>
The State Great Hural, the parliament, also decided the
government should fund the scheduled elections in the country's 21
provinces and the capital, chairman of the parliament's standing
committee of political power construction Damdingiin Demberel told
a press conference.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the parliament passed a bill to amend the
country's local electoral law, excluding proportional
representation from the existing system and shortening the
election period to three weeks from 30 days.
</P>
<P>
Observers here believe that the Mongolian People's
Revolutionary Party, which re-assumed power with an overwhelming
majority in the July parliamentary elections, will win again in
the upcoming local elections. 
</P>
</TEXT>
