<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Guangdong branch of the
Construction Bank of China (CBC) signed today a cooperation
agreement with a Guangzhou-based iron and steel group in south
China's Guangdong province.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, the bank will provide services to the
Guangzhou Iron and Steel Group. The bank will issue 2 billion yuan
(about 240 million US dollars) in loans to the group, and the
group and its subsidiary companies will open accounts at the bank.
</P>
<P>
The bank will also offer services to the company involving
settlement, consultation and assessment and act as its agent.
</P>
<P>
As one of the four groups authorized to manage State-owned
assets in the provincial capital of Guangzhou, the group has a
total assets of 15 billion yuan (about 1.8 billion dollars).
