<HEADLINE> 2000 Tibet Yadong Cultural Festival Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The 2000 China Tibet Yalong
Cultural Festival opened today in Yalong scenic spot at Zedang
Township, Shannan Prefecture in southwest China's Tibet Autonomous
Region.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the four-day festival, which has been held
successively for three years, is to help with the research and
development of Tibetan culture.
</P>
<P>
An organizer of the festival said that Shannan Prefecture has
developed rapidly over the years and the economy has been growing
at a double-digit rate.
</P>
<P>
In 1999, the average per capita income in the prefecture stood
at 1,377 yuan, higher than Tibet's average level.
</P>
<P>
Nearly 10,000 people attended the opening ceremony, which
included dancing and other performances to celebrate the event.
</P>
