<HEADLINE> China Art Portal Goes into Operation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- A Chinese art portal, china-
gallery.com, the first of its kind supplying the latest art news
and interesting information in China, has been put into operation
here.
</P>
<P>
The portal provides invaluable collections of works of art and
services for art auctions, and functions as a professional cyber
university of art, according to Siu Fai Wing, president and chief
executive officer of China Gallery Group Limited, the principal
shareholder of the portal.
</P>
<P>
The use of the cyber space helps to exhibit and promote works
of art, art auction and sale of books in an efficient way, Siu
told a media briefing here Friday. "The website enriches our
cultural life and improves artistic interflow worldwide, which
helps to lift the reputation of the nation of China," he added.
</P>
<P>
The contents of the site include art news, art people,
exclusive exhibition for sale, individual artist gallery, auction
online, cyber university of art, cartoon gallery, art books, art
forum, art life and information. 
</P>
</TEXT>
