<HEADLINE> Cambodian Premier to Attend U.N. Millennium Summit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Cambodian Prime Minister
Hun Sen will attend "The Millennium Summit of the United Nations"
to be held in New York starting from September 6 at the invitation
of Kofi Annan, secretary-general of the United Nations, according
to a press release of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs Friday.
</P>
<P>
The delegation, headed by the Cambodian premier, will include
Minister of Foreign Affairs Hor Namhong, Minister of the Cabinet
Sok An and other senior government officials, said the press
release.
</P>
<P>
Hun Sen will address the Millennium Summit of the United
Nations on September 8 while Cambodian Foreign Minister Hor
Namhong will make a speech at the 55th session of the General
Assembly of the United Nations On September 20.
</P>
<P>
While in New York, Hun Sen will also take part in the Meeting
of the Heads of State and Government of Francophone to be held on
the sidelines of the United Nations. 
