<HEADLINE> Eleven Missing in Shipwreck on Upper Reaches of Yangtze River </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WANZHOU, CHONGQING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Local rescue staff
confirmed that 11 are missing in yesterday's shipwreck on the
upper reaches of the Yangtze River.
</P>
<P>
On the way down the river, the individually-owned barge, the
Longsheng from Zhongxian County in southwestern Chongqing
Municipality, capsized in the Qutang Gorge in Fengjie County at 14:
45 Thursday. All the cargo and all the people aboard, including
nine crew members, three cargo owners and two family members, fell
overboard.
</P>
<P>
Only one owner and two crew members have been rescued so far,
according to the rescue team.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation suggests that overloading and steering
into choppy waters were the most likely causes for the accident.
</P>
