<P>
TIANJIN, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Kiev, a retired aircraft
carrier of the former Soviet Union, anchored in Tianjin, will be
converted into a tourist vessel.
</P>
<P>
Kiev served as the second generation flagship of Russian Navy
and retired in 1995. It is the largest retired ship China has ever
imported.
</P>
<P>
The Tianma Ship Dismantle Co., Ltd. of Tianjin bought it for 70
million yuan to be scrapped and then sold as waste steel. However,
it has attracted droves of visitors since it anchored at the
Tianjin Port on July 2.
</P>
<P>
A local first mate named Yang said, "It is a pity to sell it as
waste steel. When the aircraft carrier is painted after having its
rust removed it will get a new look."  
</P>
</TEXT>
