<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-Share Market Breaks Down 2000 This Week </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite Index
plunged 96.84 points or 4.16 percent on Friday to 1,999.86 points
from last week's 2,086.7 points.
</P>
<P>
The turnover this week was 66.29 billion yuan (7.99 billion US
dollars), which was 19.74 percent less than that of last week.
</P>
<P>
After having reached new highs constantly in the past seven
weeks, the Shanghai Composite Index began to decline this week and
ended lower than 2,000 points on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Technical indictors showed that the index had reached its peak
and there was the heavy pressure at the 2,100-point level. The
market may go through corrections for some time after eight months
' rises, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial
and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The shares held by the big players led the loss, and the buying
interesting was not high, however, the panic selling was gradually
weakened and the investors' sentiments became quiet.
</P>
<P>
August 31 is the deadline of the interim report period.
According to the statistics, the listed companies' interim results
were better than last year, average earnings per share were 0.1073
yuan, which was higher than last year's 0.103 yuan. 
</P>
