<HEADLINE> Rare Ceramics to Be Exhibited, Auctioned for Orphan-Aid Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Several major fine arts and
craft organizations are going to exhibit and auction 100 rare
ceramics to raise money for a national orphan assistance program.
</P>
<P>
The organizations are: China Charity Federation (CCF), China
Fine Art and Handicraft Society, China Collectors Association and
the Shanghai New Century Auction Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
This effort was announced by the four partners today at a news
conference at the headquarters of the CCF.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will be held at a local hotel September 5-6,
while the auction will take place in Shanghai September 16.
</P>
<P>
All the proceeds from the show and the auction will go to the "
Charitable Orphan Project," a program initiated by the CCF this
February.
</P>
<P>
The 100 ceramics were donated by Aixinjueluo Qimeng, a
descendant of the royal family of the Qing Dynasty (1644-1911).
Another three rare ceramics will also join the auction and the
sales will also be donated to the orphan-assistance program.
</P>
<P>
According to Yan Mingfu, president of the CCF, China has some
one million orphans. There are 30,000 of them living in orphanages
or other charitable institutions and 20,000 have been adopted by
local or foreign families. 
</P>
</TEXT>
