<HEADLINE> Foreign Tourists Arrival in Indonesia Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The number of foreign tourists
visiting Indonesia in July this year reached 383,274, an increase
of 9.71 percent compared to the figure in June which was only 349,
366, a government official announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
Chairwomen of the National Bureau of Statistic, Sudarti
Surbakti said in a press conference that cumulatively during
January-July this year, the number of tourists visiting the
country through 13 entry points reached 2,331,600 or 4.19 percent
higher from the same period last year when it was recorded 2,237,
900 tourist.
</P>
<P>
"The number of foreign tourists visiting Indonesia keeps rising
for the past two months. The vessel of the tourists arrival will
give positive contribution to the development of the national
tourist industry in the future," Surbakti said.
</P>
<P>
She also hoped that the security situation in Indonesia will be
better and better in the future. She said that the success of the
annual session of the highest law making body of the People's
Consultative Assembly has given a significant contribution to the
foreign tourists' confidence in the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
