<HEADLINE> HK Stocks Up 1.38 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks ended up 1.
38 percent Friday as blue chips generally rallied on the overnight
growth in the U.S. market.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index climbed 236.10 points to close at 17,333.61
following the 1.01 percent rise of the Dow Jones Industrial
average and the 2.5 percent increase of the Nasdaq Composite Index
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that investors are optimistic that interest rates
are little likely to rise further.
</P>
<P>
HSBC shares, the most actively traded, jumped 2.25 percent to
end at 113.50 HK dollars (14.55 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Turnover was moderate at 9.828 billion HK dollars (1.260
billion U.S. dollars), compared with Thursday's 8.565 billion HK
dollars (1.098 billion U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The properties made the best performance among the four Hang
Seng sub-index, rocketing 3.01 percent to 19,149.98, its highest
close since February 11 when it finished at 19,508.51.
</P>
<P>
The sub-index of Finance, Utilities and Commerce &AMP; Industry
advanced by 2.23 percent, 0.58 percent and 0.47 percent
respectively.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng China Enterprises Index rose 2.53 percent to 519.
87 while the Hang Seng China-Affiliated Corp Index grew by 1.33
percent to 1,369.55.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng IT Index edged down 0.31 percent to 2,764.93 and
Hang Seng IT Portfolio Index dropped by 0.93 percent to 3,368.43.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index gained 112.82 points, or 0.66 percent, to
open at 17,210.33 Friday and finished the morning session at 17,
321.24, up 223.73 points, or 1.31 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
