<HEADLINE> Shanghai A-Share Market Down Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai Composite Index
ended at 1,999.86 points, down 21.34 points or 1.06 percent on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
The turnover was 11.64 billion yuan, which was 19 percent less
than Thursday's 14.38 billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Continuing yesterday's downward trend, the market index dived
at the open again this morning, then edged above 2,000 points, but
broke through 2,000 points.
</P>
<P>
Sainty International Group Jiangsu Garments Imp &AMP; Exp Co. Ltd.
made its debut today and was the top gainer with its price up 180.
3 percent to 29.6 yuan per share, compared to its offering price
10.56 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Dongfang Boiler Group Co., Ltd. was the biggest loser. Its
price slid 8.03 percent to 11 yuan per share, hit by profit taking.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predict that the A-share market is likely to
try its supporting line of 1980-point level next week. 
</P>
