<HEADLINE> Shanghai B-Share Market Down on Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai B-share Index
fell 1.70 points, or 2.58 percent, in its third straight slide to
a fresh one-month trough of 64.48 points on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 274.56 million yuan (33.08 million US dollars ),
which was 7.49 percent less than Thursday's total.
</P>
<P>
Following yesterday's tumble, the market failed to revive amid
deteriorating sentiment and could barely trim losses off session
lows at 63.28 points in late day trading, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Only six issues rose, while 47 fell, with two unchanged.
</P>
<P>
PT Narcissus rose 4.65 percent to 0.090 U.S. dollars, while
Kaikai Indust added 2.17 percent to 0.282 US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Hainan Airlines lost 9.61 percent to 0.414 U.S. dollars, while
Yaohua Glass fell 9.55 percent to 0.398 U.S. dollars.  
