<HEADLINE> Chinese Treasuries Slump on Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- China's T-bond market slumped
and transaction value shrank by 326 million yuan to 1.52 billion
yuan Friday.
</P>
<P>
Four of the six current treasuries on the market tumbled while
two closed unchanged. The new floating-rate 010004, whose coupon
rate is 2.87 percent this year, plunged by 0.33 percent to 104.50
yuan, buoying the yield up 0.04 percentage points to 3.88 percent.
</P>
<P>
000896 and 009908 closed the session down 0.07 percent and 0.04
perent to 1,023.81 yuan and 102.95 yuan respectively. The
remaining two, 000696 and 009905, changed little, according to
Homeway, China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory
company.
</P>
<P>
China's repo market sustained the moderate active trade owing
to the tightened money supply, but repurchasing prices fell
broadly. Trade volume of three-day, seven-day, 14-day and 28-day
repurchasing transactions totaled 5.08 billion yuan, down 690
million yuan from Thursday. The interest rate of the three-day
repurchasing agreement plummeted from 4.49 percent to 0.89 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
