<HEADLINE> 1,000 Chinese Enterprises Vow to Make Good Quality Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- While the revised product
quality law was implemented in China today, 1,000 enterprises made
a joint declaration, promising to produce 100 percent qualified
products.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises pledged today at a conference marking the
implementation of the new law to upgrade product quality, compete
with their counterparts overseas, upgrade technology and set up a
market-oriented administration system.
</P>
<P>
They also vowed to make it their goal to meet the demand of
consumers, and provide fist-class products and services. They
promised to ensure that there will be no fake and inferior
products and no "improper" competition.
</P>
<P>
The enterprises called on governments, related departments,
media and customers to monitor the quality of their products.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Wu Bangguo sent a letter to the conference
saying that China should further improve product quality and crack
down on fake and inferior products.
</P>
