<HEADLINE> Indonesia Posts 0.51 Percent Inflation in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia posted a 0.51
percent inflation in August or lower than the previous month
figure when it stood at 1.28 percent, Chairwoman of the National
Bureau of Statistics(BPS Sudarti Surbakti announced here Friday.
</P>
<P>
She said that the year-on-year inflation stood at 6.11 percent.
</P>
<P>
Surbakti added that of the seven groups of consumer goods
mentioned in the consumer price index, five groups were in the
grip of inflation, namely the group of processed-foods, drinks,
cigarette and tobacco; housing healthy; transportation and
communication; and education, recreation and sports.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Surbakti said that another two groups have undergone
deflation. They are the food groups and clothing.
</P>
<P>
She also said that inflation rate during January-August this
year reached 4.71 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
