<HEADLINE> China's Fund Market on Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Most funds on the securities
investment fund market corrected, as the composite indexes on the
two stock markets in Shanghai and Shenzhen continued to move
downwards on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Among the 30 funds, four funds rose, eight funds remained
unchanged, and the rest declined. But in general, the 22
discounted funds moved steadily, basically fluctuating 0.01 yuan
around the price levels of the last close, according to Homeway,
China's leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
However, restructured funds clearly dropped. Those that fell
more than one percent were all restructured funds. Fund Tongzhi
and Fund Yuhua dropped the most, down 4.4 percent and 3.05 percent.
</P>
<P>
The 22 funds had long been in the discounted trading, making
their price levels bolstered by performances and intrinsic values.
All interim reports had been released recently, current price
levels of most funds were lower than assets value per fund unit
and face values.
</P>
<P>
But the restructured funds' price levels are usually higher
than their own NAVs and it was easy for them to perform actively
when the market was good. Speculation funds played an important
part in the trading.
</P>
<P>
The fund index on the Shanghai stock market closed at 1,051.73
points, down 1.67 percent compared to that of the last week; the
fund index on the Shenzhen stock market ended at 1,061.77 points,
down 1.64 points compared to that of the last week. 
</P>
</TEXT>
