<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-Share Market Weekly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Composite Index
deceased 25 points or 3.9 percent to 611.46 points on Friday. The
sub-index ended at 4,784.58 points, down 3.4 percent from last
Friday's close.
</P>
<P>
Turnover this week stood at 59.93 billion yuan (7.22 billion US
dollars), which was 17.37 percent more than that of last week.
</P>
<P>
After having reached new highs constantly in the past seven
weeks, the Shenzhen stock market began to decline this week and
dropped to 611 points on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The technical indictors showed taht the index had reached its
peak and there was a heavy pressure at the 640-point level. The
market may go through corrections for some time after eight months
' rises, according to Homeway, China's leading on-line financial
and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The shares held by big players led the loss, and the buying
interesting was not high, however, the panic selling was gradually
weakened and investors' sentiments became quiet.
</P>
<P>
August 31 is the deadline of the interim report period.
According to the statistics, the listed companies' interim results
were better than last year, average earnings per share was 0.1073
yuan, which was higher than last year's 0.103 yuan. But altogether
117 companies reported losses for the first half, 44.44 percent
more than the end of 1999.
</P>
<P>
Investors' concern is focused on the market expansion,
including the IPO, the second board and the listing of state-owned
enterprise shares. The government policies will also influence the
market.  
</P>
