<HEADLINE> CPPCC Vice Chairman Meets Overseas Taiwan Entrepreneurs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Zhang Kehui, vice-chairman of
the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), met here today with a visiting
delegation of noted overseas Taiwan entrepreneurs.
</P>
<P>
In his talks with the delegation, headed by Rosano Yan, Zhang
briefed the visitors about the economic situation in China and
expressed his hopes that mainland entrepreneurs and companies
would increase their cooperation with overseas Taiwan businessmen
and enterprises.
</P>
<P>
The 16-member delegation has been visiting in China at the
invitation of the Sub-committee for Hong Kong, Macao and Taiwan
Compatriots and Overseas Chinese of the CPPCC National Committee
and the All-China Federation of Taiwan Compatriots.
</P>
<P>
Before visiting Beijing, the overseas Taiwan businessmen
delegation had toured northeastern Heilongjiang, Jilin and
Liaoning provinces. 
</P>
</TEXT>
