<HEADLINE> Philippines' Exports Up 12.8 Percent in July </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' merchandise
exports rose 12.8 percent year-on-year to 3.21 billion U.S.
dollars in July against the year-ago 2.85 billion dollars, the
government said Friday.
</P>
<P>
The National Statistics Office (NSO) said in a press release
that for the January-July period, the country's total exports were
valued at 20.83 billion dollars, up 1.7 percent from the year-
earlier 18.65 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Electronics components, the country's top export item,
accounted for 57.9 percent of the aggregate receipt, the NSO said,
adding that sales of this commodity group, valued at 1.86 billion
dollars, represented a 5.8 percent increase over 1.76 billion
dollars in July 1999.
</P>
<P>
Agro-based products, ranking second among major export groups,
accounted for 4.7 percent of the total for July while their sales
rose by 26 percent to 150 million dollars from 119 million dollars
last year, it added.
</P>
<P>
Posting an 11.9 percent upswing in receipts and accounting for
90.6 percent of aggregate earnings, manufactured goods netted 2.91
billion dollars, up from 2.60 billion dollars a year earlier, the
NSO said.
</P>
</TEXT>
