<HEADLINE> Shenzhen A-Share Market Down at Friday Close </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen Composite Index
closed at 611.46 points on Friday, down 5.96 points or 0.97
percent compared with last close. The sub-index closed at 4,784.58
points, which was down 41.72 points or 0.86 percent from the last
close.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 10.3 billion yuan, 29.11 percent less than
Thursday's 14.53 billion yuan, according to Homeway, China's
leading on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
Continuing yesterday's downward trend, the market index dived
to open again, then edged above 611 points, but sharply down when
the market closed.
</P>
<P>
The shares held by big players were on the loser's list. The
panic selling gradually faded away and investors' sentiments
became quiet.
</P>
<P>
Tonghua Goldhorse Medicine Co., Ltd., Jilin, China was the top
gainer with its price up 9.98 per cent to 19.95 yuan per share.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Shengdao Group Co., Ltd. was the biggest loser. Its
price shed 6.66 percent to 10.51 yuan per share, hit by profit
taking.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts predict that the market is likely to try its
support line of 600 points next week. 
