<HEADLINE> Shenzhen B-Share Market Down Friday </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Shenzhen B-Share Index
slipped 1.13 points, or 0.95 percent to close at 118.28 points on
Friday, coming off its intraday high of 120.82.
</P>
<P>
Turnover was 100.94 million HK dollars, which was 48.68 percent
less than Thursday's total, according to Homeway, China's leading
on-line financial and securities advisory company.
</P>
<P>
The market managed to rally this afternoon. After reaching the
intraday low of 117.99 points, the index closed at a low level.
</P>
<P>
The market ended a volatile but range-bound trading session and
virtually closed down as the buying momentum dwindled in late
trade Furthermore, the market met some profit-taking pressure as
well this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Gainers lagged behind losers by 16 to 34, with six unchanged.
</P>
<P>
Zhonghao rose 5.36 percent to 0.59 Hong Kong dollars, while
Changchai extended 2.81 percent to 2.93 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Health Mineral fell 6.97 percent to 4.27 HK dollars, while
Shenzhen Seg declined 5.13 percent to 2.32 HK dollars.
</P>
<P>
Homeway analysts say that with the technical correction, the
market will continue to consolidate, as investors have been so
dependent on earnings for direction and the broad upward trend is
not likely to come in the short term.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
