<DOCNO> XIE20000901.0180 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand to Develop "Technical Textile" Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Thai textile industry is
developing new products, called technical textile, aimed to
increase business opportunities and competitiveness in the world
market, the Thai News Agency (TNA) said here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Permanent Secretary of Industry Ministry Manu Liewpairoj was
quoted as saying that the Thai textile industry is applying the so-
called technical textile to the production of variety of products.
</P>
<P>
The technical textile will become a key raw material over the
next five years. It is made from plastic fiber, used to substitute
traditional fiber to help enhance the industry's potential, he
said.
</P>
<P>
Thai textile products made from the technical textile are
targeted to be increased to 10 percent of total production,
doubling from currently five percent, over the next five years, he
stated.
</P>
<P>
The Institute of Development of Thai Textile Industry would
provide useful advices and guidelines for local manufacturers to
alter their production basis to the technical textile, he
disclosed.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Mana Sethabutr, Director of the Institute of
Development of Thai Textile Industry was quoted as saying that
studies had shown that technical textile products would have high
potential in the world market, as the new material would play
increasing role in the production of textile products.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturers in foreign countries currently use the technical
textile by about 40 percent, compared to five percent in Thailand;
so, the institute is pushing for doubling the use of technical
textile to 10 percent over the next five years, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Sale of Thai textile products in the international market
accounts for around 500-600 billion baht (about 12.5-15 billion U.
S. dollars) annually, with exports in the first seven months of
this year increasing by 16 percent over the same period of last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
