<HEADLINE> Macao to Host Fireworks Display Contest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The 12th Macao International
Fireworks Display Contest will be held here from September 9 to
October 1, a tourism official said at a press conference Friday.
</P>
<P>
Joao M. Antunes, director of the Tourist Office of the Macao
Special Administrative Region (SAR) government, said ten teams
will take part in the contest.
</P>
<P>
The teams will come from countries and regions include the
Philippines, Australia, Germany, Japan, Thailand, Portugal,
Britain, Switzerland, and China's mainland and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The teams will give fireworks shows on the nights of September
9, 12, 16, 23 and October 1. Each night, two teams will stage
shows with each lasting about 18 minutes.
</P>
<P>
Local tourism authorities began to host the first spectacular
fireworks display contest in 1989 to enliven the life of residents
and attract more tourists.  
