<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Inflation in Switzerland Lowest in 10 Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The annual rate of inflation in
Switzerland fell back to 1.3 percent in August, its lowest level
since last November, according to the country's federal office for
statistics Friday.
</P>
<P>
The August rate was sharply lower than the previous month when
inflation was two percent. The federal office for statistics
attributed the drop to lower transport costs, mainly due to a fall
in oil prices, and lower prices for clothing and shoes during the
cut-price "sales" period.
</P>
<P>
The price of oil, a key factor in the inflation rate, is set to
rise again but this has not affected the August consumer price
index, the statistics office said.
</P>
<P>
In its breakdown of prices, the statistics office noted
slightly higher prices for food and rented accommodation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
