</P>
<P>
Teaching materials of most Chinese schools exceed the actual
capability of the students, according to Yang Deren, dean of
chemistry department of Shanghai Normal University.
</P>
<P>
Under the burden of school work, some students lost interest in
studying, he added.
</P>
<P>
The 2000 Summer Teaching Material Catalog for Primary and
Middle Schools was published by MOE this year, which deleted 39
volumes of teaching material to lessen the study load.
</P>
<P>
Li hopes that more time will be spent in enlarging student's
knowledge, as well as the ability to develop analytical thinking
and reading. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000901.0191 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Product Quality Law Implemented in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The newly revised law on
product quality came into effect today to offer effective legal
guarantee for China's quality promotion.
</P>
<P>
In the coming five to ten years, economic competition will
focus on quality competition, and the improvement of China-made
products will be a key factor in China's economic development,
said Li Chuanqing, director of the State Bureau of Quality and
Technical Supervision.
</P>
<P>
The amended product quality law includes 74 articles. The
original version had 51.
</P>
<P>
Li said at a meeting marking the implementation of the new law
here today that under the revised law, anyone selling fake or
inferior products will be severely punished.
</P>
<P>
The revised law further defines the responsibility for the
government to improve product quality and stresses that
enterprises must accept supervision from the quality control
departments.
</P>
<P>
China launched a series of clampdowns on fake and shoddy
products in recent years. However, the production of poor-quality
products is still a serious problem, especially in small
enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Li said that it is urgent to set up systems of quality
responsibility, strict quality administration, technical
renovation and after-sale service in enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that local quality and technical supervision
departments should help local governments include quality
upgrading into the social and economic development plan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
