<HEADLINE> Phreatic Eruption at Mayon Volcano in Southern Luzon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Mayon Volcano in the southern
tip of Luzon island occurred an ash-driven explosion Friday
afternoon, Philippine Institute of Volcanology and Seismology (
Phivolcs) said.
</P>
<P>
The Phivolcs said in a press statement that a phreatic eruption
of Mayon volcano spewing, at around 2:21 p.m. (0600 GMT), thick
ash as high as 50 feet from its crater.
</P>
<P>
The ashes drifted towards the southeast portion fronting St.
Domingo town in Albay province, which lies on the southern tip of
Luzon island, the statement noted.
</P>
<P>
The explosion also caused the collapse of pyroclastic deposits
at the crater of the volcano, it added.
</P>
<P>
Local officials said that there is nothing to worry because the
sudden phreatic eruption is normal. 
</P>
