<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 1 (Xinhua) -- India's exports stood at 13.
84 billion U.S. dollars in the first four months of the 2000-2001
fiscal year (April-July), up 24.43 percent from 11.04 billion
dollars recorded a year ago.
</P>
<P>
