by 24.82 percent during the period, were put at 17.56 billion
dollars in April-July as against 14.07 billion dollars in the
previous fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the total exports in July were valued only at 3.55
billion dollars, an increase of 16.46 percent over 3.05 billion
dollars in July 1999.
</P>
<P>
The monthly imports in July were valued at 4.29 billion dollars
against 3.57 billion dollars in July 1999, netting a gain of 20.12
percent. 
