<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Railways Leases Track to Private Company </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 1 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh Railways for the
first time in its nearly three decades of operational activities,
has recently leased out 40-kilometer long track from Jessore to
Benapole, in the southwest part of the country, the Independent
reported on Friday.
</P>
<P>
An agreement to this effect reached recently, will enable a
private company to look after the track from October 1. This is
part of the overall plan of the Railways to involve private sector
in its activities to improve the quality of maintenance and
service and also to make the organization modern and viable.
</P>
<P>
Railway authorities will provide necessary materials for the
maintenance of the line, while the contractor company will be
responsible for supplying labor and maintain the track for which
they will receive 15 thousands U.S. dollars per annum.
</P>
<P>
The amount will be lesser than the expenditure Bangladesh
Railways used to incur in the past to maintain the line. However,
the overall supervision of the maintenance will be looked after by
engineers of Bangladesh Railways.
</P>
<P>
The process of integration of private sector in Bangladesh
Railways' activities started in 1997 and till now it is confined
to commercial activities (selling and checking of tickets and
cleaning the coaches) and on board service (provide attendants in
coach and catering services).
</P>
<P>
At the moment 10 pairs are being operated and the process have
almost been completed for operating commercial activities in
another 31 pairs. Against operation of three pairs of on board
service, the process is near complete to allow two more pairs.
</P>
<P>
`The running of the trains under private management has
encouraged more passengers to use trains meaning greater revenue
earning for the Railways.
</P>
<P>
Compared to 3,022,000 passengers carried by Railways in July
last year, the number of users grow to 3,375,000, an increase of
12 per cent. The revenue rise was from 0.23 million dollars to 0.
25 million dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
