<HEADLINE> 14 Killed in Sri Lanka's Mine Blast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 1 (Xinhua) -- At least 14 Sri Lankan air
force personnel were killed on Friday when a tractor they were
travelling in hit a land mine in the north of the country.
</P>
<P>
A military spokesman said eight others were wounded in the
powerful blast set off by separatist Liberation Tigers of Tamil
Eelam (LTTE) rebels.
</P>
<P>
He said the blast happened on a road between the government-
held town of Vavuniya and the western Mannar district when the air
force personnel were returning from a route clearing patrol.
</P>
<P>
Government troops in the area are confronting LTTE rebels who
are fighting for an independent homeland in the north and east of
Sri Lanka since 1983. 
</P>
