<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Seize Another 410 White-Owned Farms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwean government has
gazetted another 410 commercial White-owned farms for compulsory
acquisition, bringing the total number of such properties to 1,952,
The Herald reported Friday.
</P>
<P>
The government first gazetted 804 farms or a total of 2.2
million hectares, and then a further 229 farms with a total of 574,
659 hectares. Only last week, it gazetted 509 farms, measuring a
total of one million hectares.
</P>
<P>
The government has announced to compulsorily acquire 3,041
farms or a total of five million hectares for resettlement of
landless blacks.
</P>
<P>
Land, Agriculture and Resettlement Minister Joseph Made on
Wednesday told Parliament that the government will successfully
resettle people on five million hectares before the onset of the
rain season. 
</P>
