<DOCNO> XIE20000901.0222 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Biggest APCT Production Line Being Built in Qinghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
APCT, which combines the advantages of plastic and metal, is an
environment-friendly material that is corrosion-proof, and can
survive both high and low temperatures. It can be widely used in
supplying water, gas transmission and cooling equipment.
</P>
<P>
Experts say the production line will be armed with an
ultrasonic welding technique to raise the plasticity of tubes.
</P>
<P>
The Qinghai Lutong Plastic-steel Door and Window Plant and the
Guangdong Foshan Jinshitong Development Co. Ltd. have invested 115.
8 million yuan (about 13.9 million U.S. dollars) in the project.
</P>
<P>
The project, to be completed by March next year, can produce 50,
000 tons of aluminum-plastic compound tubes annually. The annual
output value will be 120 million yuan (about 14.4 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Experts predicted that 80 percent of the water-supplying pipes
in urban and rural areas would be made from APCT by 2010. 
</P>
</TEXT>
