<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Residents To Pay For Garbage Collection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- From this month, Beijing
residents as well as temporary residents will pay to have their
garbage collected.
</P>
<P>
 Each household shall pay three yuan (0.36 U.S. dollar) each
month beginning as of today, while temporary residents, working
families from outside Beijing, shall pay two yuan (0.24 U.S.
dollar), according to today's "Beijing Morning Post."
</P>
<P>
But low income families will be exempted from the charge
according to local governments, said the paper.
</P>
<P>
The charge is in addition to the levy imposed by local
neighborhood committees for collecting and removing domestic
garbage. The move is expected to help improve Beijing's garbage
disposal capability.
</P>
<P>
Beijing has also imposed surcharges on tap water early this
year to fund the operation of waste water treatment plants.
</P>
</TEXT>
