<HEADLINE> Xinhua World Economic News Summary at 0430 GMT, August 31 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA -- Brazilian President Fernando Henrique Cardoso and
his Venezuelan counterpart, Hugo Chavez, Thursday agreed to
promote integration between the South American Common Market (
Mercosur) and the Andean Community of Nations (CAN) in view of
establishing a free trade area between the two blocs.
</P>
<P>
This was made known Thursday in a joint communique published by
Brazil's Foreign Ministry.(Brazil-Venezuela-Integration)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PANAMA -- Panama's Technical Judicial Police (JTP) broke up a
criminal network of counterfeiting U.S. dollars on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,400 dollars with the denomination of 10, 20, 50
and 100 were seized and six people detained, among them one
Colombian and five Panamanians, said JTP sub-director Javier
Cherigo, adding that Panama's police would continue crackdown on
organized crime.(Panama-Counterfeit Money)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BUCHAREST -- An Official report reveals that Moldovan
commercial banks took in 1.63 billion lei( about 132.1 million U.S.
dollars) in total deposits in the first half of this year,
according to reports from Chisinau.
</P>
<P>
The report shows that deposits in Moldovan commercial banks
increased 25 percent in the first six months of this year from the
same period last year. (Moldova-Deposits)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Mexico has made a decision to pay its debt of 3.
2 billion U.S. dollars to the International Monetary Fund (IMF),
Finance and Public Credit Secretariat (SHCP) announced Thursday.
</P>
<P>
This decision was made at a meeting of the Commission of
Exchanges and attended by the SHCP and the Bank of Mexico,
Mexico's central bank.(Mexico-IMF)
