<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Panama Breaks Up Money Counterfeiting Network </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Panama's Technical Judicial
Police (JTP) broke up a criminal network of counterfeiting U.S.
dollars on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A total of 10,400 dollars with the denomination of 10, 20, 50
and 100 were seized and six people detained, among them one
Colombian and five Panamanians, said JTP sub-director Javier
Cherigo, adding that Panama's police would continue crackdown on
organized crime.
</P>
<P>
He did not disclose more details because the investigation was
still underway.
</P>
<P>
It was believed that the case was probably linked with the
other gangs which were broken up earlier. Three policemen were
involved in the case and expelled afterwards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
