<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mexico to Pay IMF Debt  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
This decision was made at a meeting of the Commission of
Exchanges and attended by the SHCP and the Bank of Mexico,
Mexico's central bank.
</P>
<P>
Mexico's current foreign exchange situation is much improved
after Mexico successfully fulfilled its fiscal and monetary
objectives these past few years, said SHCP.
</P>
<P>
Mexico has repaid some 3 billion dollars to IMF in the last
fiscal year from July 1999 to July 2000. Statistics show that
Mexico now owes IMF 3.2 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
IMF granted loans to Mexico to help the country surmount
domestic economic problems in 1995, according to SHCP.
</P>
<P>
Analysts said the outgoing President Ernesto Zedillo's payment
to IMF would relieve the economic burden on the new President
Vicent Fox, who will take office at the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
High oil prices on the international market this year have
boosted Mexico's economy. Oil income in the first half of this
year increased by 1,002.2 percent from the same period in l999.
</P>
</TEXT>
