<HEADLINE> Costa Rica Seizes 800 Pounds of Marijuana </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, August 31 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rican agents seized 800
pounds of marihuana in an operation Wednesday night in San Jose,
the capital of the Latin American country, said Public Security
Minister Rogelio Ramos on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Three vehicles were seized and four suspects detained, among
whom are two Costa Ricans, one Colombian and one Panamanian, said
Ramos.
</P>
<P>
The marihuana was contained in 181 packages in 12 bales, with
each package containing about 4.4 pounds of marijuana, he said.
</P>
<P>
The two suspects from Colombia and Panama had no legal
residence permits, Ramos noted.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigations indicated that the marijuana was
smuggled from Colombia and will be distributed in Costa Rica.
</P>
</TEXT>
