<HEADLINE> Moldovan Commercial Banks Report an Increase in Deposits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, August 31 (Xinhua) -- An Official report reveals
that Moldovan commercial banks took in 1.63 billion lei( about 132.
1 million U.S. dollars) in total deposits in the first half of
this year, according to reports from Chisinau.
</P>
<P>
The report shows that deposits in Moldovan commercial banks
increased 25 percent in the first six months of this year from the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Among the growth, deposits were 240 million lei (about 19.4
million U.S. dollars), or 35 percent higher; while deposits in
foreign exchange rose 43 million lei (about 3.5 million U.S.
dollars), or 6 percent higher.
</P>
<P>
The rising bank deposits came under surprising circumstances of
falling interest rates. The annual interest rate for deposits is
about 25.23 percent this year, 2.56 percentage points off from the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Experts said the stability of foreign exchange rates was the
main reason for rising deposits. Statistics show that the exchange
rate between lei and the U.S. dollar has been within the narrow
band of 12.30 to 12.70 lei to one U.S. dollar, since the beginning
of this year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Loans offered by Moldovan commercial banks to
foreign countries reached 1.8 billion lei (about 145.9 million
dollars) in the first half of this year, which was one percent
higher than the level of the same period last year. The annual
lending rate is currently 34.67 percent, 0.62 percentage points
lower than that of the same period last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
