<DATE_TIME> 2000-09-01 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China to Launch Major Scientific Program for Western Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 1 (Xinhua) -- The Ministry of Science and
Technology has decided to launch a major science promotion program
for the national drive to develop the western region in the
following five years.
</P>
<P>
The ministry decided to provide strong scientific and
technological support for sustainable economic and social
development of the region by fostering a research team that can
solve major regional technological problems.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry's five-year science promotion program
(2001 to 2005), China is to concentrate on industrialization of
scientific discoveries and providing traditional industrial
ventures with advanced technology.
</P>
<P>
The ministry is also to strengthen the building of major basic
research labs, major science programs and engineering centers.
</P>
<P>
The five-year program is also to help speed up development of
high and new technology industries and to offer more support to
high-tech development zones in Xi'an, Chongqing, Lanzhou, Chengdu
and other major cities in the western region.
</P>
<P>
The ministry plans to promote scientific and technological
cooperation between coastal areas and western areas as well as
international scientific cooperation towards China's western
provinces and autonomous regions.
</P>
<P>
Advanced foreign technology, experts and capital are also
welcomed for the scientific promotion program.
</P>
<P>
The building of information networks, digital libraries and e-
commerce is also part of the five-year program.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has provided 278 million yuan (about 21 million U.
S. dollars) for scientific promotion projects in western areas
this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
